Regular walking, running or cycling is a great way to stay active.!
Being active helps lower stress hormones such as cortisol and promotes the release of feel-good hormones, such as endorphins.

Physical activity also helps to keep your immune system working effectively as it flushes bacteria from the lungs and airways, increases white blood cell circulation and raises body temperature, all of which help the body fight infection.

Warm Rotaract Greetings!

We are all well aware of the battles our health workers are facing on the frontline in this unprecedented crisis. Lack of government preparedness, panic buying among citizens and shortages are leaving the health workers without PPEs needed the most during this time.

RaCKMC, in collaboration with Protech Nepal have come up with an initiative "FIGHTING FOR FRONTLINERS" to help raise funds for NATIONWIDE DISTRIBUTION OF LOCALLY MANUFACTURED PERSONAL PROTECTIVE EQUIPMENTS.

It will be a 3-week program starting from tomorrow, August 23rd to September 12th 2020 which will include: 

- Fund collection via e-sewa, Khalti app and GoFundMe for international donors.

- Online PUBG tournament in joint collaboration with our sister clubs ( Rotaract Club of KDC, 
  Rotaract Club of Reliance and Rotaract Club of Kathmandu North ) : which will be held on the 2nd week 

- Nationwide Mock Test for MBBS, BDS & Nursing program : which will be held on the 3rd week 

We are accepting donations through
E-sewa: 9840011588, 9813298716
Khalti: 9813298716
GoFundMe: https://gf.me/u/x9ncwx
Please mention your name and initiatives' name "Fighting For Fronliners" while donating

For queries, contact:  9841894388

Hoping for your continued support.

Regards, 
Rotaract Club of Kathmandu Medical College

ANEURYSM:

A ballooning and weakened area in an artery.

Aneurysms often occur in the aorta, brain, back of the knee, intestine or spleen.

 A ruptured aneurysm can result in internal bleeding and stroke. It can sometimes be fatal.

node.text: I know i tried to make a come back to this a few weeks ago but I dont think i was far enouppgh out of the woods to do so and even this time im not 100% sure but what do I have to loose by trying?? The truth is that im far from the end of healing completely from years of mental pain and illness but i finally feel like I'm in the mental head space of being able to get trough this. I was really hopping through the pandemic I would post regularly to keep an accurate record of what life was like when the world was shut down but in reality that makes my 'diary' so much more real because during my darkest days I was basically a ghost to the world around me. As for the future of this account im going to try my best to keep updating and posting. As I heal from my own traumas I hope ill be able to  inspire others to reach out and talk about their problems with professionals because after all a problem shared is a problem halved. I hope that eventually this will make a beautiful recovery story and turn into a space filled with only love and  positivity. I hope to feel confident enough to share parts of my story with you in the near future because mental illness is the realist thing in today's world and no one should ever suffer alone. Its okay not to be okay and its okay to ask for help when you're struggling. My inbox is always open if you need someone to talk to, you will get through this ü¶ãüíô

I took this photo and would you believe it was around lunchtime on a weekday, yet I managed to get the intersection free of traffic! I assume this is how it looks today, but for all the wrong reasons. Let’s stay focused and positive that it won’t be long and we can bring life back into our streets, suburbs, cities, states and around the world with health and happiness ‚ù§Ô∏è I hope you are doing well ‚ù§Ô∏è

Stay Safe Little One
“A Story about a big virus and many little warriors.”
***PROFITS WILL BE DONATED see more down below...
There are so many people writing books for kids in COVID 19, I have knocked back a lot of these books as I do think it’s just to overwhelming BUT....this  little one I have taken on as it’s to the point in a lovely rhyming based book that is small in size, easy to understand and ends positively AND these great people are donating all profits minus what was spent on publishing to a Hospital in Montreal COVID 19 relief fund. üëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèªüëçüèª
ü¶† üåà 
BOOK INFO
ü¶†üåà
“...Parents of young children everywhere are trying to make sense of their emotions while parenting during the unprecedented Covid-19 global pandemic.  Ensuring our children feel safe and happy is our main priority.”
“One day soon, life will return to normal, until then here is a short story that will inform small children about staying safe all the while unleashing the power of their imagination to help them visualise a brighter future.”
ISBN 978-1-7772-94106
Ages 5 - 7yrs
Softcover Edition
Written by Claudia Amato & illustrated by Jennifer Nozzolillo 
@staysafelittleone

Image may contain: indoor, text that says 'Robot Servers Ready to Overtake a New Hot Pot Restaurant on the Las Vegas Strip X Pot opened its lounge at the Grand Canal Shoppes, but the robots await their turn to serve when the dining room debuts By Susan Stapleton August 20, 2020 3:00 pm'.

node.text:
The robots do not function yet, but the food is ready at X Pot, the new hot pot restaurant now open at the Grand Canal Shoppes at the Palazzo. The restaurant opened its lounge area, with the dining room with robot servers debuting later.
Once completely open, the restaurant promises an entertainment experience with 360-degree projections in high-def, interactive light shows, and themed sounds to accompany the thousand-year-old Sichuan hot-pot tradition.
Founders Haibin Yang and David Zhao of Chubby Cattle fame in Chinatown bring the restaurant with its Asian fusion dishes, complete with A5 Wagyu beef and certified Kobe beef dry-aged for 100 days in a case in the dining room. Customers then can select the quality and level of meat, based on how long the beef has been aged. Diners also choose and cook their own ingredients, ranging from meat and seafood to vegetables, and cook them at communal tables.
For now, the lounge offers a tight menu of oyster shooters, wagyu beef sushi, seafood platters, and marinated cherry tomatoes.
When the dining room opens, X Pot will feature performances that include ancient Chinese face-changing ceremonies, noodle dances, and table animation shows, each paired with its smart-robot technology. (Article by Eater Las Vegas)  #cocktailwaitresses #bottlegirls #lasvegas #pandemic #covid #robot

What’s in the $2.2 trillion stimulus for defense?

RealClearDefense

FOREIGN AND DEFENSE POLICYDEFENSE

Mackenzie Eaglen

@MEaglen

March 28, 2020

#PresidentTrump recently called himself¬†a #wartime president¬†for confronting a #pandemic that threatens the lives and livelihood of so many Americans. Congress heard the (bugle) call and responded with what #SenateMajorityLeader #MitchMcConnell (R-KY) called a “wartime level of investment¬†into our nation.”
Calling #coronavirus (#COVId19) the “#invisibleenemy,”ü§£ü§£ the president has called for “shared sacrifices” and a “response¬†unseen since World War II.”
The president is getting a hefty fiscal fix through a $2 trillion stimulus spending bill moving to his desk shortly for signature. Spanning nearly twenty years of conflict, the #warsinIraq and #Afghanistan cost the #taxpayer¬†roughly $1.5 trillion dollars ü§îü§î by comparison.
The stakes are high, and no one is immune. The military is ramping up to support state and local authorities in responding to the pandemic. The Department of Defense is also confronting the rise of infected servicemembers, families, and defense civilians, all while it deals with impacts on the defense industrial base — the Defense Department needs this new funding.
Defense spending in the stimulus totals $10.5 billion, with likely more to come later. Of this, $1 billion is allocated to the Defense Production Act (DPA), and the bill waives several restrictions to supercharge it for pandemic recovery. Other priorities include $1.5 billion for working capital funds, $1.2 billion for uniformed personnel, $2 billion for Operations and Maintenance, nearly $5 billion for the Defense Health Program, and $2.8 million for the Armed Forces Retirement Home.
This funding demands strident¬†supervision. Mark Cancian from the Center for Strategic and International Studies¬†explained that¬†the Defense Department’s original request for supplemental emergency funds involved the creation of a “slush fund.” Congress rejected the concept and used various provisions to strike a helpful¬†balance between the immediate funding needs of the U.S. military .

One of the most famous studies of obedience in psychology was carried out by Stanley Milgram, a psychologist at Yale University. He conducted an experiment focusing on the conflict between obedience to authority and personal conscience.

65% (two-thirds) of participants continued to the highest level of 450 volts. All the participants continued to 300 volts.

Conclusion - Ordinary people are likely to follow orders given by an authority figure, even to the extent of killing an innocent human being.  Obedience to authority is ingrained in us all from the way we are brought up.

People tend to obey orders from other people if they recognize their authority as morally right and/or legally based. This response to legitimate authority is learned in a variety of situations, for example in the family, school, and workplace. 

"The extreme willingness of adults to go to almost any lengths on the command of an authority constitutes the chief finding of the study and the fact most urgently demanding explanation." - Stanley Milgram

This right here is something that should be known far and wide. This experiment proves the absolute importance of psychology, both of the Individual and the Crowd, and showcases just how much blind belief in any authority figure is one of the most dangerous belief that exists in our world today. What one needs to understand is that we live in a society that is run by those who do NOT have the best interest of Humanity at heart. They have a very advance Knowledge of Human Psychology and know exactly which buttons to press to make an Individual tick the way they want him/her to tick.

In case you still did not catch the very basic essence of this experiment and the horrors blind belief in authority does... NOT ONE participant categorically REFUSED to Harm another human  because the "authority" asked them to. They ALL went along with it, some more than others.
This blind belief in authority is one half of the equation... the other is the importance of Morality in a person's Life, and why, when it is lacking, people will do anything and justify it.

ANASTROPHE MIXTAPE LINK IN BIO

ANASTROPHE explores the various psychologic stages in which we understand and confront the current pandemic's potential to open portals: the frightening futures this difficult time_s could bring to our now past-world and to our loved ones, the post-apocalyptic scenarios we can't even materialize or prepare for, and even the dangerous "back to normal" game; all the possibilities invade our minds everyday as we experience little doses of hope, sadness, madness, euphoria and loss.

ANASTROPHE is an attempt to rebuild and compile alive dreams/nightmares, address personal ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§Ø‡§æs through sound compilation.

ANASTROPHE is inspired by Arundhati Roy's text ‘The (COVID-19) pandemic is a portal’, and Eugenio Tisselli's diary/essay ‘Entretiempos (parte I)’ THIS AUDIO CAN DEVELOP SEVERAL ANASTROPHIC CIRCUMSTANCES. UNKNOWN FUTURES IN SELF-CONFIGURATION, POTENTIAL ENERGY.

ANASTROPHE was premiered at @internetpublicradio 25th May 2020

Tracklist and Anastrophe Portal Map included.

Thank you Eugenio Tisselli, for the support.

Update: There's a demo-mixtape titled ANASTROPH > E from may that includes songs from @colinself and Vessel in my Mixcloud account.

This is a difficult time, a scary time, an unpredictable time. It's also been a difficult, scary and unpredictable year. Many people were already under stress from the #pandemic when the fires broke out, and tensions have only heightened over the last few days.

Mental health has been a recurring topic this year, and we need to ensure we're taking care of ourselves both mentally and physically, ever more so now. And because stress can affect anyone, the Red Cross also has disaster mental health and spiritual care workers available to help people cope.

Red Cross Disaster Mental Health workers work virtually and in-person to meet the emotional needs of disaster clients, communities, and other Red Cross disaster workers. They identify individuals who need additional support, provide short-term disaster mental health interventions, and refer individuals to local resources as necessary. 

If you are at an evacuation center or Red Cross-supported shelter and would like to speak with a Disaster Mental Health worker, please let the Red Cross workers know. We're here to help.

If you've been impacted by the wildfires and need Red Cross assistance, please call 1-800-REDCROSS.

Its funny how you go on Instagram  and type the hashtag ‘selfie’ and theres 429 Million users, yet if you put in #saveourchildren theres only 147 thousand users of the hashtag.
Are we really a self absorbed nation? don’t get me wrong, i do love posting some selfies, raunchy pics, having a yarn with you all. But last but not least, i do love responding to the entertainers in my dm’s.
BUT THERES MORE TO OUR PROFILES THEN JUST WHAT EVERYONE ELSE WANTS TO SEE. 

As a mother of two incredible little humans, I cannot begin to fathom what our millions of babies around the world feel when they are ripped from the arms of their parents, kidnapped, boxed in a crate across borders like a wild animal.
Sexually, physically, emotionally, and mentally tortured for life. 
It brings anxiety to my actual self whenever i try to begin to wonder what if that was my baby? unfortunately a million of these babies (infants-18 year olds) are someones BABIES!
There’s no time like a pandemic to spread awareness, most of us are at home with our babies, access to the internet, home schooling, keeping safe.
i’m sure that when we go to the toilet for that 5 minutes we think we’ll get in peace is enough time to even post the hashtag #saveourchildren, we all have time! I’m sure we all have five fucking minutes. 

IM SORRY TO ALL OUR BABIES THAT ARE MISSING IN 2020 I HOPE FOR CHANGE!!
OUR BABIES NEED US, THEY ARE SCARED, HURT, BEING RAPED, ABUSED AND ALMOST EVERYTHING ELSE YOU CAN IMAGINE, open your eyes please!! WAKE UP AND #saveourchildren #savethechildren

node.text: @pbrookin That is fantastic! So glad you were able to do something good and special for yourself in the midst of all of this chaos.
I love the pink and purple! üíúüíó I finally got a haircut after 8 months and went from brunette to blonde.  It was a huge moral booster for me!!! üíõ
Besides awesomely fun hair, you also have a very cool mask! Can I ask where you found it?
@pbrookin That is fantastic! So glad you were able to do something good and special for yourself in the midst of all of this chaos.

I had a delightful five-year-old ask me on tour last week if I got in trouble when I died my hair purple and pink. I had a good laugh about it then, but the question has stayed with me. While I didn’t get into trouble, of course, I do wonder how long I will keep it this way. And the answer, like so many answers these days, is that I just don’t know.
.
The easy explanation as to why I did it is simple – why not? Nothing else makes sense right now…might as well have purple and pink hair. A slightly more honest answer is that as my gray roots really started to make themselves SEEN and KNOWN they were not doing much for my brown ends. The colors were simply not getting along nicely. So, to stop the fight between brown and gray I introduced pink and purple and there has been much more hair harmony since then.
.
I have returned to the hair salon for cuts – I’ve been twice now – but I don’t think I’ll ever go back to younger-me-brunette. The gray is slowly taking over and the pink and purple are both temporary colors that slowly wash out and have to be refreshed every couple of weeks. So, someday I’ll probably stop with the pink and purple and get a full-on view of the gray. A “new me” in the “new world” I’m kinda excited about it, to be honest.
.
But right now I like having purple and pink hair. It makes me smile. Plus, I’ll always know what pictures were taken during the pandemic. And, instead of everything just FEELING different, I actually LOOK different. It feels right right now.
.
Hope you are doing something that a five-year-old might think you’d get into trouble for, but you’re just doing because it makes you feel like you are doing *something* in a world where there is currently so much we can’t do. Thankfully, we can get out and tour again. Let me know if you’d like to! I’m easy to find at our starting location – I’m the one with the pink and purple hair. #purplehair #pinkhair  #pandemichair #nothingmakessense

Repost from @lauriehoey using @RepostRegramApp - “Rapper #IceCube criticized members of the #DemocraticParty following this past week's #convention, saying that despite all the fanfare, no speakers talked about "a contract with #BlackAmerica."

The hip-hop icon and actor urged Black Americans to make both parties "earn that vote." Speaking on Instagram Saturday, he ridiculed speakers at the Democratic National Convention (#DNC) for only talking about voting #PresidentDonaldTrump out of office in the upcoming #election.

Ice Cube said small businesses with Black owners were left out of the trillions spent by #Congress during the #coronavirus #pandemic, and he doesn't think #Democrats have a plan for how to help struggling #minoritycommunities moving forward.”

And he’s absolutely 100% correct. They do have a plan though, to enrich themselves while we continue to struggle. I wish more people would wake up to understand that a vote is EARNED, not owed. And we certainly don’t owe the DNC anything seems all they’ve done for us is disenfranchise and suppress our voices then gaslight us into thinking we HAVE NO CHOICE but to vote for them. This #twopartysystem must be abolished. Along with this corrupt capitalist, racist system that keeps the black, brown and poor communities down. We need to focus our attention on a new party because #TheDems have made it CLEAR they have NO intention of releasing their death grip on OUR party. It’s now controlled by #WallStreetBankers, #millionaires and #lobbyists. Why do you think our #taxpayerdollars are ALWAYS bailing out #WallStreet and huge corporations (not small businesses as Ice Cube stated)?! They do not care about us so we must organize for @peoplespartyus and defeat both parties which are actually one in the same. #BidenHarris2020 #Trump2020 #NEVERBiden #NEVERKamala #NEVERTrump #VoteGreenParty2020 #MamaTurner #APeoplesParty #PeoplesParty #NinaTurner2024 #BlackLivesMatter

Not long ago, after I participated  in the palliative care Australia painting competition, a friend suggested me that I should paint more medical related topics. This time I chose a very controversial one... Vaccines. 

From a medical professional point of view (as I am) .Vaccinations prevent sickness and death associated with infectious diseases such as  measles, polio and whooping cough, they also hold up broader gains in education and economic development.

In this current pandemic climite a new vaccine could be the solution to the problem and will allow  the pupulation to gain  immunity without getting sick, but developimg a vaccine is not easy and require  many many  testing and our scientists are in a race agains time and COVID-19. Recently, we heard of some advances in this regard... but we might still be a few months away.

We have been told the end is coming. Mom has a fever, shallow breathing, trouble swallowing, pains and is not responding. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
I printed out this photo for her to have by her bed. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
We had a video call today and told her we loved her. We made some jokes and hoped she would hear them. We talked about her favorite Hallmark movies and told her the fall movies were starting soon. We said we’d come to see her and hug her and bring her chicken wings as soon as we could. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
I think she’ll see her parents and her brother long before she sees us again.  But she will know she was loved on this earth beyond measure and she will know that even though we cannot be with her that our love and strength are right there beside her. (She is in a Covid nursing home and is very infectious and we have been strongly warned of the risks)‚†Ä
‚†Ä
It’s crazy to me that she fought Alzheimer’s tooth and nail and it is Covid that has knocked the fight right out of her. This is truly the worst possible ending I could have NEVER imagined. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Please keep my sweet Mom in your thoughts and prayers. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä

Every year there is a carbon global resource budget that fluctuates depending on current trends in economic growth, environmental causes, and global matters.

This year we have reached our budget by August 22nd 2020, and consumed our entire budget for the year. 

This year compared to last is seen a whole month later, (which is great!) but partially due to the pandemic, where 2020’s carbon foot print fell by 14.5%. This date has not moved in a positive direction since the 1980s!! ‚ú®

The move of the date is due not because of efforts for the earth or environmental outreach but due to the suffering through the pandemic. 

üîëBut from these findings if we can learn and make intentional efforts to ensure environmental sustainability for the perceived year we could see potential growth for the better.
